The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Broadband tariffs 

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Feb. 22: AirTel Broadband and Telephone Services today announced new broadband tariffs for its residential and business users in the north and central parts of the country.

 These tariff packages, available at multiple price points, would enable customers to choose the most suitable package depending on their usage. These packages include the flexi-plan, which offers customers the flexibility to utilise the monthly charges either on Internet or voice or both. 

 AirTel currently provides broadband and telephone services in Delhi, Haryana, Uttar Pradesh-west (Noida), Madhya Pradesh, Chhattisgarh, Karnataka and Tamil Nadu and has more than 1 lakh DSL customers in its circles of operation. 

 AirTel currently offers broadband services in bandwidth packages of 64 kilobits per second (Kbps), 128 kbps, 256 kbps, 384 Kpbs and 512 kbps. 

 Targeted at homes, small and medium enterprises (SMEs) and large companies, the service is scaleable depending on the usage. 

 AirTel is offering a ?Turbo Starter pack? at Rs 249 per month for speeds up to 64 kbps. 




